.Dd January 16, 2003
.Dt SIGHOLD 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm sighold
.Nd manipulate current signal mask
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libc
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include \*[Lt]signal.h\*[Gt]
.Ft int
.Fn sighold "int sig"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Bf -symbolic
This interface is made obsolete by
.Xr sigprocmask 2 .
.Ef
.Pp
The
.Fn sighold
function adds the signal
.Fa sig
to the calling process' signal mask.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
If successful, the
.Fn sighold
function returns 0.
Otherwise \-1 is returned and
.Va errno
is set to indicate the error.
.Sh ERRORS
The
.Fn sighold
function will fail if:
.Bl -tag -width Er
.It Bq Er EINVAL
The argument
.Fa sig
is not a valid signal number.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr sigprocmask 2 ,
.Xr sigrelse 3
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Fn sighold
function conforms to
.St -p1003.1-2001 .
